# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AutoFactoryDashboard — environment variables
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev. In production, set these in Vercel.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Required ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# GitHub fine-grained Personal Access Token with READ-ONLY access to your
# factory repos. Repository permissions (all Read-only):
#   Contents · Pull requests · Issues · Actions · Metadata
# See the README ("Create the GitHub token") for click-by-click steps.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Single shared password for the dashboard's auth gate. Pick something strong.
# NOTE: if this is left blank the gate is DISABLED and the dashboard is public.
DASHBOARD_PASSWORD=

# ── Optional · AI summaries (briefing, per-project digests, launch summary) ──
#
# The dashboard uses an LLM for the factory briefing, per-project did/now/next
# digests + headlines, and the completed-project "what was built" summary.
# Provider preference: GEMINI_API_KEY first (reliable free tier), else
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY. With neither set, deterministic templated text is shown.

# Google Gemini — free tier, no card. Get a key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash

# OpenRouter (OpenAI-compatible). Free model slugs rotate and can rate-limit;
# Gemini above is the more reliable default. Key: https://openrouter.ai/keys
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free

# ── Optional · History & trend charts (Vercel KV) ────────────────────────────

# Injected automatically when you attach a Vercel KV / Upstash Redis store to the
# project. If absent, trend sparklines are hidden and the daily cron is a no-op.
# The app also accepts the UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL / UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN
# names that the Upstash marketplace integration injects — either pair works.
KV_REST_API_URL=
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
# KV_REST_API_READ_ONLY_TOKEN=

# ── Optional · Cron protection ───────────────────────────────────────────────

# If set, the daily snapshot route requires `Authorization: Bearer <secret>`.
# Vercel sends this header automatically for scheduled cron invocations.
CRON_SECRET=
